knitr document van Steensel lab

LAD rewiring data: F1ES TRIPclones .

Bas van Steensel, Feb - May 2019.

Introduction

Here I revisit Laura’s plotting and analysis of her rewiring data in the TRIP-derived clones with multiple integrated PGK promoters. This script plots potential figure panels for Figure 8.

Version history

Description of Data

  • Simple read counts per GATC fragment. Split by Cast/129 allele.
  • Data reprocessed (aligned using WASP) by Tom van Schaik

Path, Libraries, Parameters and Functions

Inspect data

How noisy are the data? Do they correlate well overall? Looks OK?

#scatter plot of Control vs Exp data:
notna<-!(is.na(mcols(sDamID.CM1417.129)$logratio) | is.na(mcols(sDamID.CM1417.CAS)$logratio))
s<-sample(which(notna), 50000)
par(mfrow=c(1,1))

#correlation coefficients:

#use loess smoothing to straighten out banana-shapes etc:
#the reasonable assumption here is that most of the genome will remain unaffected, or at least will not show effects in the same direction.
#ord<-order(mcols(sDamID.Control)$logratio[s])
LOESS50<-loess(mcols(sDamID.CM1417.CAS)$logratio[s]-mcols(sDamID.CM1417.129)$logratio[s] ~ mcols(sDamID.CM1417.129)$logratio[s], span=0.5)
#apply correction to experimental data:
mcols(sDamID.CM1417.CAS)$logratio <- mcols(sDamID.CM1417.CAS)$logratio - predict(LOESS50, mcols(sDamID.CM1417.129)$logratio)
#plot again: 
plot(mcols(sDamID.CM1417.129)$logratio[s], mcols(sDamID.CM1417.CAS)$logratio[s], pch=19, cex=0.5, col="#00000022", main="CM1417")
LMcor<-lm(mcols(sDamID.CM1417.CAS)$logratio[s] ~ mcols(sDamID.CM1417.129)$logratio[s])

abline(a=0, b=1, col="black", lty="dashed", lwd=3)

Align and combine DamID data of LAD integrations and controls

#make list of smoothed datasets for easier access:
Smthd<-list(CM1417.129S1=sDamID.CM1417.129, CM1417.CAST=sDamID.CM1417.CAS, CM1420.129S1=sDamID.CM1420.129, CM1420.CAST=sDamID.CM1420.CAS)
LADIP<-as.data.frame(int_pos_LADstate) #easier subsetting
ww<-which(LADIP$LADstate=="LAD") #only LAD integrations

CWINSIZE<-length(ww)*SMTH #runwin size to be consistent with SMTH, considering that we are merging length(ww) integration sites.
if (CWINSIZE %% 2 == 0) CWINSIZE<-CWINSIZE+1
DscoresI<-c() #all DamID scores around all integrations
DscoresC<-c() #all DamID scores around the same sites in the control allele
DdistI<-c() #corresponding distances to integration sites
DdistC<-c() #corresponding distances to corr control sites

MRG<-1e5 #how big is the window around the integration site for which to get data
otherallele<-c("129S1","CAST"); names(otherallele)<-c("CAST","129S1") #trick to pick the other allele
par(mfrow=c(7,4), mar=c(0.5,0.5,0.5,0.5))
for(i in ww)
{print(i)
 #get DamID data around integration site
 subI<-subsetByOverlaps(x=Smthd[[paste(LADIP$clone[i],LADIP$allele[i], sep=".")]], ranges=int_pos_LADstate[i], maxgap=MRG)
 scoresI<-mcols(subI)$logratio
 #get DamID data around control site:
 subC<-subsetByOverlaps(x=Smthd[[paste(LADIP$clone[i],otherallele[LADIP$allele[i]], sep=".")]], ranges=int_pos_LADstate[i], maxgap=MRG)
 scoresC<-mcols(subC)$logratio
 #distance to integration site:
 dddI<-mid(subI)-mid(int_pos_LADstate[i])
 dddC<-mid(subC)-mid(int_pos_LADstate[i])
  #invert coordinates if strand==-1:
 if(as.vector(strand(int_pos_LADstate[i]))=="-"){dddI<- -1*dddI; dddC<- -1*dddC}
 #add to cumulative vector:
 DscoresI<-c(DscoresI, scoresI)
 DscoresC<-c(DscoresC, scoresC)
 DdistI<-c(DdistI, dddI)
 DdistC<-c(DdistC, dddC)
 Ylim<-quantile(c(DscoresC, DscoresI), c(0.05, 0.95), na.rm=TRUE)+c(-0.3, 0.3)
 plot(dddI, scoresI, type="l", col="darkred", xlab="", ylab="", xaxt="n", yaxt="n", ylim=Ylim)
 lines(dddC, scoresC, col="navy")
 abline(v=0, col="orange", lty="dashed")
 abline(h=Ylim, lty="dashed", col="grey")
}

#calculate mean curves:
O<-order(DdistC)
DscoresIo<-DscoresI[O]
DscoresCo<-DscoresC[O]
DdistO<-DdistI[O]
nas<-which(is.na(DscoresIo) | is.na(DscoresCo))
if(length(nas)>0)
   {DscoresIo<-DscoresIo[-nas]
    DscoresCo<-DscoresCo[-nas]
    DdistO<-DdistO[-nas]
   }

DscoresIo<-runmed(DscoresIo, k=CWINSIZE)
DscoresCo<-runmed(DscoresCo, k=CWINSIZE)
DdistO<-runmed(DdistO, k=CWINSIZE)


plotfun<-function()
  {par(mfrow=c(1,1))
   par(mgp=c(2,0.8,0), mar=c(4,4,2,2))
   plot(DdistO/1e3, DscoresCo, type="n",
     xlab="position relative to integration site (kb)",
     ylab=expression("log"[2]*"(DamID ratio)"),
     xlim=c(-70, 70),
     ylim=DynRng*1.1)

 #fill in with polygons:
 df<-data.frame(start=DdistO/1e3, E=DscoresIo, C=DscoresCo)
  df$sign<-sign(df$E-df$C)
  df<-df[!is.na(df$sign),]
  df$switch<-c(0,diff(df$sign))/2
  df$segment<-cumsum(abs(df$switch))
  for(seg in unique(df$segment))
  {p<-which(df$segment==seg)
  xvals<-c(df$start[p], rev(df$start[p]))
  yvals<-c(df$E[p], rev(df$C[p]))
  shade<-ifelse(df$sign[p[1]]==1, "#FF000022", "#0000FF22")
  polygon(xvals, yvals, border=NA,col=shade)
  }

 #add data lines:
  lines(df$start, df$E, col="darkred", lwd=2)
  lines(df$start, df$C, col="navyblue", lwd=2)

  #mark genome-wide quantiles :
  abline(h=DynRng, lty=c("dotted","dashed"), col="grey", lwd=2)

  #mark integration site
  abline(v=0, col="darkgrey")

  #sliding window size: 
  WS<-mean(diff(DdistO, CWINSIZE))
  lines(x=c(-70, -70+WS/1e3), y=c(-1.5, -1.5), lwd=4)
}

plotfun()


pdf(file=paste0("LAD_rewiring__TRIPclones_DamID_runningmean_BvS", Date, ".pdf"), width=6, height=5)
plotfun()
dev.off()
